@page "/"

<PageTitle>Home</PageTitle>

<h1>There is always a bigger snake...</h1>

Welcome to the snake pit.
<br/>
May your slithers carve the land before you.
<br/>

<br/>
We started the design process with the 5 models in the Models folder, Point2D first as it is more foundational to the others for drawing. We 
added network connection and started building network controller and SnakeGUI. World has maintaining state methods
in it as well and would store the status of the world in dictionaries of each parsable JSON object from server parsed from Network Controller. 
Each dictionary would represent an object: walls, snakes, and power-ups. This would be the foundation of the project.
Snake GUI will start the game, in which all objects and world would be drawn in based on the world state per frame. As server sends in parsable data for walls, powerups,
and handling of the snakes, the GUIs job is to draw all the objects correctly with the correct state.
<br/>

<br/>
In proper MVC order -> Player enters info and clicks connect (View) -> a connection is opened from NetworkController (Controller) and starts to recieve server info -> game loop loads and 
draws in frames with OnAfterRenderAsync (View) with help from the model classes to maintain world info and state (Models)
<br/>

<br/>
We did a good job of following expected MVC protocol in this complex game assignment. We believe with everything from the testable given server- our
assignment functions correctly after extensive learning, development time and debugging. We hope you enjoy our game and thank you!
<br/>

<br/>

Noteable features:
<br/>
Outside of world map image the background is red
<br/>
Powerups give you a +1 indicator when you eat them (creative)
<br/>
Your snake flashes light green when you grow (score changes) (creative)
<br/>
If you cant connect (ex: wrong port), a error message will display with only a retry button. However, port and server entries
must be correct
<br/>
Snake can be controlled with computer arrow keys and "W","D", "S", "A"
<br/>
Snake color is generated by using provided player ID with 8 different colors to be assigned.
<br/>
At snake died (hit wall or hits other snake), player respawns to new location. At disconnect, player can newly rejoin with new snake at new location


<br/>

<br/>

Changes since PS10: 
<br/>
Database configuration with web server up to spec  accessed at localhost
<br/>
Key functionality:
Similar to spec, if ai clients terminated, all get that disconnected time. If player (user) disconnects, everyone + AI
gets same disconnect time. Database is located at connection string. If multiple clients opened (browsers), treated as different
games. 

